    {
      "id": "9872311f12d4707663d88706b896d2573a659314",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 292,
        "name": "James Nunez",
        "email": "jnunez@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jnunez"
      },
      "date": "2017-07-07 22:13:27.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nThis patch is good and does exactly what it should do, but I think we should wait to land it. Here's why ...\n\nI was looking at the results from the testing for this patch and was wondering why the newly added tests (actually, removed from ALWAYS_EXCEPT list) were running so quickly; 2 or 3 seconds. They are fast because all they do is call echo. \n\nI think we need to investigate if these tests should be restored to their original functionality or if they are no longer needed.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "45ef5c38325432c948aa61a72fb950f45692ee1e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 292,
        "name": "James Nunez",
        "email": "jnunez@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jnunez"
      },
      "date": "2017-07-24 21:36:57.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nLooking back to the original bugzilla ticket that created performance-sanity.sh, test 1 and 2 never had anything but the existing cal to echo. Thus, we should just remove those two tests from the test script.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
